---
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Starboard | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer, Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Starboard</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Starboard is a New Zealand-based maritime intelligence platform that helps
      you monitor vessel activity in real-time. Whether you're a government
      official protecting marine ecosystems, a border security team tracking
      suspicious vessels, or a researcher combating illegal fishing, you can
      spot patterns and take action when it matters most.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Built alongside government users across New Zealand, Australia, and the
      Pacific, the platform processes over 4,000 vessel positions per second.
      This means you get the real-time intelligence you need to make informed
      decisions quickly, without waiting for outdated reports or manual data
      processing.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I joined Starboard part-time to collaborate with their Chief of Product
      and Chief of Marketing, to improve their web experience, inline with their
      global ambitions.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Website Redesign</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Government agencies and maritime organizations were struggling to find
      what they needed on Starboard's outdated website. Researchers looking for
      illegal fishing case studies, border security teams seeking vessel
      tracking capabilities, and conservation officers needing real-time alerts
      couldn't easily discover the right tools for their specific missions.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I conducted a comprehensive content audit and sitemap restructure, working
      with Sales and Customer Success to understand exactly what different users
      were trying to accomplish. The new approach presented what we believed was
      a more intuitive structure for officials and researchers to quickly find
      relevant case studies, technical documentation, and the specific
      intelligence solutions they need.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/starboard-website-one.png"
      alt="Homepage design showcasing maritime surveillance expertise and global reach."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/starboard-website-two.png"
      alt="Solutions page highlighting real-time vessel tracking and analytics capabilities."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I designed and built over 20 pages on Webflow while migrating 100+
      existing articles, ensuring that prospects could easily find case studies,
      technical documentation, and solution details relevant to their specific
      maritime challenges. Each page was crafted with different user types in
      mind—from conservation researchers to border security teams.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The redesign was completed in 3 months, delivering clearer product
      positioning and a browsing experience that helps officials and maritime
      researchers quickly understand how Starboard's platform fits into their
      daily workflows: whether they're investigating suspicious vessel activity
      or monitoring protected marine areas.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/starboard-website-three.png"
      alt="Resource center design organizing maritime intelligence insights and case studies."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/starboard-website-four.png"
      alt="About page emphasizing team expertise and company mission in ocean protection."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
</Layout>
